.npr.org/blogs/goatsandsoda/2014/11/06/362054623/sierra-leones-refugee-all-stars-are-refugees-again-from-ebola\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Read more</span></a>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<strong>Health professionals to provide weekly updates on Ebola</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Centers for Disease Control and Prevention is collaborating with the World Health Organization and other partners in response to the ebola epidemic.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There will be a document that summarizes the important happenings in response to the outbreak, and will be regularly updated with new information.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The virus has been limited to a small area of West Africa located in Sierra Leone and Western Guiniea.</span>\r\n\r\n<b><a href=\"http://vaccinenewsdaily.com/stories/510644447-health-professionals-provide-weekly-update-on-ebola\">Read more</a></b>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Suspected Ebola Relapse Could be the First</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pauline Cafferkey who contracted the Ebola virus from Sierra Leone has been exhibiting symptoms that could be indicators of a relapse. Cafferkey is a U.K. patient that worked in Sierra Leone but had recovered from the disease and was released from a hospital.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.ischoolguide.com/articles/30710/20151024/ebola-scare-complications-uk-crozier.htm\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Read More</span></a>", "Ebola News", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "111-revision-v1", "", "", "2015-10-30 18:02:27", "2015-10-30 18:02:27", "", "111", "http://ideafoundation.tk/111-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `gxd_posts` VALUES("187", "1", "2015-11-02 21:00:36", "2015-11-02 21:00:36", "<div class=\"n diyfeLiveArea\"></div>\n<div class=\"n diyfeLiveArea\">\n<div id=\"textWithImage-6206134804\" class=\"clearover\">\n<div class=\"align-container imgright\"><a href=\"http://ideafoundation.tk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/sierra-leone-map.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-190\" src=\"http://ideafoundation.tk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/sierra-leone-map.png\" alt=\"sierra leone map\" width=\"182\" height=\"158\" /></a></div>\nSierra Leone is on the Atlantic coast of West Africa. Named dubbed as \"lion mountain\" by a 15th-century Portuguese explorer. Sierra Leone was a British colony from the early 19th century until 1961.\n\nSierra Leone is a small nation in West Africa which is in the process of rebuilding after a brutal, decade-long proxy war.  A democratically elected government was installed in 2007 and the country is slowly, but surely rebuilding.  Currently conditions within the country, while improving, are still among the worst in the world.\n\nSierra Leone is blessed with tropical climate and diverse environment ranging from the savannah to the rainforest.With coastal rainfall reaching 495 cm. (195 inches) annually,a it is one of Western Africa’s wettest places. Mangrove swamps lie along the coast, with wooded hills and a plateau in the interior. The eastern region is mountainous.\n<ul>\n	<li>1 in 2 young women cannot read</li>\n	<li>1 in 9 children die before the age of 5</li>\n	<li>1 in 11 women die from pregnancy or childbirth</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nThere is a great need for education in Sierra Leone. Unhealthy living conditions slow progress as the population struggles with illnesses as AIDS is prevail and because of the recent Ebola outbreak and now possible relapse on the disease. Education on the diseases and how to prevent them would be beneficial and have a great influence on the  However, as literacy spreads, so does the know-how to improve healthcare and sustain infrastructure development.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIDEA is proud to work with the people of Sierra Leone to share knowledge and strengthen families and communities. We are honored to provide technical assistance as the people of Sierra Leone build a country that only they could make.\n\n</div>\n</div>", "Sierra Leone", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "40-autosave-v1", "", "", "2015-11-02 21:00:36", "2015-11-02 21:00:36", "", "40", "http://ideafoundation.tk/40-autosave-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
