INSERT INTO `gxd_posts` VALUES("325", "5", "2015-11-10 08:04:28", "2015-11-10 08:04:28", "<div class=\"n diyfeLiveArea\">\r\n<div id=\"textWithImage-6206134804\" class=\"clearover\">\r\n<div class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-190\" src=\"http://ideafoundation.tk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/sierra-leone-map.png\" alt=\"Sierra Leone Image Map\" />\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Map of Sierra Leone</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Sierra Leone is on the Atlantic coast of West Africa. Named dubbed as \"lion mountain\" by a 15th-century Portuguese explorer. Sierra Leone was a British colony from the early 19th century until 1961.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sierra Leone is a small nation in West Africa which is in the process of rebuilding after a brutal, decade-long proxy war. A democratically elected government was installed in 2007 and the country is slowly, but surely rebuilding.  Currently conditions within the country, while improving, are still among the worst in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sierra Leone is blessed with tropical climate and diverse environment ranging from the savannah to the rainforest.With coastal rainfall reaching 495 cm. (195 inches) annually,a it is one of Western Africa’s wettest places. Mangrove swamps lie along the coast, with wooded hills and a plateau in the interior. The eastern region is mountainous.</p>\r\n<p><ul>\r\n	<li>1 in 2 young women cannot read</li>\r\n	<li>1 in 9 children die before the age of 5</li>\r\n	<li>1 in 11 women die from pregnancy or childbirth</li>\r\n</ul></p>\r\n<p>There is a great need for education in Sierra Leone. Unhealthy living conditions slow progress as the population struggles with illnesses as AIDS is prevail and because of the recent Ebola outbreak and now possible relapse on the disease. Education on the diseases and how to prevent them would be beneficial and have a great influence. As literacy spreads, so does the know-how to improve healthcare and sustain infrastructure development.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>IDEA is proud to work with the people of Sierra Leone to share knowledge and strengthen families and communities. We are honored to provide technical assistance as the people of Sierra Leone build a country that only they could make.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>", "Sierra Leone", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "40-revision-v1", "", "", "2015-11-10 08:04:28", "2015-11-10 08:04:28", "", "40", "http://ideafoundation.tk/40-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `gxd_posts` VALUES("326", "5", "2015-11-10 08:07:51", "2015-11-10 08:07:51", "<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In 1998, during the decade-long Diamond War, many of current members of the IDEA Board of Directors felt moved to action. Sierra Leone was underdeveloped before the war, and is still struggling to return to pre-war standards. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The first projects were small: a brick making tool here, an electric generator there. As the the projects grew, the group formed the International Development and Education Alliance (IDEA) Foundation. IDEA was granted its 501(c)3 status in 2007.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">PROGRAM PARTNERS</span></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">IDEA works with program partners with established networks in Sierra Leone. Our partners include:</span><p>\r\n<p><ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Books for Africa</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Evangelical Lutheran Church in Sierra Leone</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Forgotten Diamonds</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heart to Heart International</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heifer International</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">MediSend</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Water2Thrive</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">West Africa Fistula Foundation</span></li>\r\n</ul></p>\r\n<h3><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">IDEA FOUNDATION HISTORY</span></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">2003</span></strong></h4> \r\n<p>The Women\'s Education and Vocational Program began receiving funds from the IDEA Foundation.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">2007</span></strong> </span></h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">501(c)3 status granted by the IRS. IDEA Executive Director visited Sierra Leone. Nursing students began attending Njala University with full financial support. Site for the Calaba Town clinic identified and renovations began. </span>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400; color: #B95E05;\"><strong>2008</strong> </span></h4>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Calaba Town Clinic renovations continued.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">2009</span></strong> </span></h4>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heifer International returned to Sierra Leone with co-sponsorship from the IDEA Foundation. IDEA\'s Executive Director participated in opening day at the Calaba Town Clinic when 300 patients were served. \"Peace and Rebuilding\" event was celebrated by over fifty people at First Unitarian Society of Denver. Sale of holiday cards began to fund K-8 textbooks and library books; and books for the school of public health at Njala University.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">2010</span></strong> </span></h4>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First class with IDEA-sponsored nurses graduated from Njala University. Construction of clean water wells began. IDEA celebrated its first annual gala and the creation of 2,000 farms. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">2011 </span></strong></h4>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Collaboration began with the West Africa Fistula Foundation, which has facilities in Bo. IDEA sent a forty-foot container to Sierra Leone filled with medical equipment and supplies for the Calaba Town Clinic and the West Africa Fistula Foundation. IDEA celebrated its Second Gala and the creation of 4,000 farms.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong><span style=\"color:#B95E05;\">2012</span></strong> </span></h4>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Our third annual gala and auction, spring, grow, thrive was held on May 12 in Richardson, Texas.  There were around 100 attendees and our friends at the Krio Descendants Union were featured in the Dallas Morning News in conjunction with the event.  Our Executive Director Jennifer Seaborn, and volunteer Andrew Wisniewski visited our program sites.   </span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">2013</span></strong> </span></h4>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">IDEA provided continuing support for the Cabala Town Clinic, the Women\'s Literacy Center and Heifer International.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">2014</span></strong></h4>\r\n<p><ul>\r\n	<li>IDEA continues to provide support for the Cabala Town Clinic and the Women\'s Literacy Center.</li>\r\n	<li>Two 40-foot containers of medical equipment were sent through MediSend. IDEA also contributed to the shipment costs for an additional container of medical equipment via Brother\'s Brother.</li>\r\n	<li>IDEA\'s 5th annual fundraiser, Hope &amp; Health Benefit Concert and Auction, was held November 29th at the historic Lakewood Theater in Dallas, TX. The show featured Sierra Leone\'s Refugee All Stars.</li>\r\n</ul></p>\r\n<h4><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">Other Projects </span></strong></h4>\r\n<p><ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heart to Heart relief boxes of medicine were sent to the Cabala Town Clinic and the West Africa Fistula Foundation.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sonogram Equipment was sent to the Modia Clinic in Lungi</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Co-sponsorship of a 40 foot container of books via Books for Africa</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">IDEA\'s 4th Annual Fundraiser, the Fabric of Hope Gala and Auction, was help May 11. </span></li>\r\n</ul></p>\r\n", "IDEA", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "84-revision-v1", "", "", "2015-11-10 08:07:51", "2015-11-10 08:07:51", "", "84", "http://ideafoundation.tk/84-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `gxd_posts` VALUES("327", "5", "2015-11-10 08:15:02", "2015-11-10 08:15:02", "<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In 1998, during the decade-long Diamond War, many of current members of the IDEA Board of Directors felt moved to action. Sierra Leone was underdeveloped before the war, and is still struggling to return to pre-war standards. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The first projects were small: a brick making tool here, an electric generator there. As the the projects grew, the group formed the International Development and Education Alliance (IDEA) Foundation. IDEA was granted its 501(c)3 status in 2007.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">PROGRAM PARTNERS</span></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">IDEA works with program partners with established networks in Sierra Leone. Our partners include:</span><p>\r\n<p><ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Books for Africa</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Evangelical Lutheran Church in Sierra Leone</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Forgotten Diamonds</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heart to Heart International</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heifer International</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">MediSend</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Water2Thrive</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">West Africa Fistula Foundation</span></li>\r\n</ul></p>\r\n<h3><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">IDEA FOUNDATION HISTORY</span></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">2003</span></strong></span></h4>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Women\'s Education and Vocational Program began receiving funds from the IDEA Foundation.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">2007</span></strong> </span></h4><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">501(c)3 status granted by the IRS. IDEA Executive Director visited Sierra Leone. Nursing students began attending Njala University with full financial support. Site for the Calaba Town clinic identified and renovations began. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400; color: #B95E05;\"><strong>2008</strong> </span></h4>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Calaba Town Clinic renovations continued.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">2009</span></strong> </span></h4>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heifer International returned to Sierra Leone with co-sponsorship from the IDEA Foundation. IDEA\'s Executive Director participated in opening day at the Calaba Town Clinic when 300 patients were served. \"Peace and Rebuilding\" event was celebrated by over fifty people at First Unitarian Society of Denver. Sale of holiday cards began to fund K-8 textbooks and library books; and books for the school of public health at Njala University.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">2010</span></strong> </span></h4>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First class with IDEA-sponsored nurses graduated from Njala University. Construction of clean water wells began. IDEA celebrated its first annual gala and the creation of 2,000 farms. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">2011 </span></strong></h4>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Collaboration began with the West Africa Fistula Foundation, which has facilities in Bo. IDEA sent a forty-foot container to Sierra Leone filled with medical equipment and supplies for the Calaba Town Clinic and the West Africa Fistula Foundation. IDEA celebrated its Second Gala and the creation of 4,000 farms.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong><span style=\"color:#B95E05;\">2012</span></strong> </span></h4>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Our third annual gala and auction, spring, grow, thrive was held on May 12 in Richardson, Texas.  There were around 100 attendees and our friends at the Krio Descendants Union were featured in the Dallas Morning News in conjunction with the event.  Our Executive Director Jennifer Seaborn, and volunteer Andrew Wisniewski visited our program sites.   </span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">2013</span></strong> </span></h4>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">IDEA provided continuing support for the Cabala Town Clinic, the Women\'s Literacy Center and Heifer International.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">2014</span></strong></h4>\r\n<p><ul>\r\n	<li>IDEA continues to provide support for the Cabala Town Clinic and the Women\'s Literacy Center.</li>\r\n	<li>Two 40-foot containers of medical equipment were sent through MediSend. IDEA also contributed to the shipment costs for an additional container of medical equipment via Brother\'s Brother.</li>\r\n	<li>IDEA\'s 5th annual fundraiser, Hope &amp; Health Benefit Concert and Auction, was held November 29th at the historic Lakewood Theater in Dallas, TX. The show featured Sierra Leone\'s Refugee All Stars.</li>\r\n</ul></p>\r\n<h4><strong><span style=\"color: #B95E05;\">Other Projects </span></strong></h4>\r\n<p><ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heart to Heart relief boxes of medicine were sent to the Cabala Town Clinic and the West Africa Fistula Foundation.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sonogram Equipment was sent to the Modia Clinic in Lungi</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Co-sponsorship of a 40 foot container of books via Books for Africa</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">IDEA\'s 4th Annual Fundraiser, the Fabric of Hope Gala and Auction, was help May 11. </span></li>\r\n</ul></p>", "IDEA", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "84-revision-v1", "", "", "2015-11-10 08:15:02", "2015-11-10 08:15:02", "", "84", "http://ideafoundation.tk/84-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `gxd_posts` VALUES("328", "5", "2015-11-10 08:15:51", "2015-11-10 08:15:51", "<p>Operated by the <a href=\"http://elcsl.weebly.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Evangelical Lutheran Church of Sierra Leone</a>, Calaba Town Clinic operates in the eastern part of Freetown. The low-cost clinic is available to the entire community and helps address little health concerns before they become life-threatening issues.</p>\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_246\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"140\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-246\" src=\"http://ideafoundation.tk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/clinic.png\" alt=\"Calaba Town Clinic Director, Nurse Juliana M\'bayeilla, shows off a well-stocked pharmacy cabinet.\" width=\"140\" height=\"153\" /> Calaba Town Clinic Director, Nurse Juliana M\'bayeilla, shows off a well-stocked pharmacy cabinet.[/caption]\n\n<p>Services include: midwife-assisted delivery, prenatal care, infant and well-mother exams, wound care, screening for high blood pressure and diabetes, and many other vital services.</p>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<h4>The Calaba Town Clinic:</h4>\n<p><ul>\n	<li>Promotes the health of individuals and families in the community;</li>\n	<li>Provides continuity of care for individuals at high risk; and</li>\n	<li>Frees hospital emergency rooms to handle more dire cases.</li>\n</ul>\n</p>", "Calaba Town Clinic", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "245-autosave-v1", "", "", "2015-11-10 08:15:51", "2015-11-10 08:15:51", "", "245", "http://ideafoundation.tk/245-autosave-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `gxd_posts` VALUES("329", "5", "2015-11-10 08:16:01", "2015-11-10 08:16:01", "<p>Operated by the <a href=\"http://elcsl.weebly.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Evangelical Lutheran Church of Sierra Leone</a>, Calaba Town Clinic operates in the eastern part of Freetown. The low-cost clinic is available to the entire community and helps address little health concerns before they become life-threatening issues.</p>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_246\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"140\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-246\" src=\"http://ideafoundation.tk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/clinic.png\" alt=\"Calaba Town Clinic Director, Nurse Juliana M\'bayeilla, shows off a well-stocked pharmacy cabinet.\" width=\"140\" height=\"153\" /> Calaba Town Clinic Director, Nurse Juliana M\'bayeilla, shows off a well-stocked pharmacy cabinet.[/caption]\r\n\r\n<p>Services include: midwife-assisted delivery, prenatal care, infant and well-mother exams, wound care, screening for high blood pressure and diabetes, and many other vital services.</p>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h4>The Calaba Town Clinic:</h4>\r\n<p><ul>\r\n	<li>Promotes the health of individuals and families in the community;</li>\r\n	<li>Provides continuity of care for individuals at high risk; and</li>\r\n	<li>Frees hospital emergency rooms to handle more dire cases.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>", "Calaba Town Clinic", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "245-revision-v1", "", "", "2015-11-10 08:16:01", "2015-11-10 08:16:01", "", "245", "http://ideafoundation.tk/245-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `gxd_posts` VALUES("330", "5", "2015-11-10 08:26:42", "2015-11-10 08:26:42", "<p><a href=\"http://www.westafricafistulafoundation.org/\" target=\"_blank\">The West Africa Fistula Foundation</a> operates a surgery center in Bo, Sierra Leone. Caused by obstructed labor, an obstetric fistula is a hole between birth canal and bladder. If left untreated a fistula leads to infection and to personal hygiene issues, including urine leakage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is not unusual for women suffering from fistula to be shunned by their families and become beggars in one of the poorest countries on earth.</p>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_249\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"157\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-249\" src=\"http://ideafoundation.tk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/repair-surgery.png\" alt=\"A patient awaits her turn for fistula repair surgery.\" width=\"157\" height=\"158\" /></a> A patient awaits her turn for fistula repair surgery.[/caption]\r\n\r\n<p>Fewer than half of all child births in Sierra Leone are attended by any trained professional, such as a midwife, nurse, or doctor. Often no one is available to offer treatment when complications arise, as they do in approximately 15% of all births. This can lead to disabling injuries like fistula, and even death. One in eleven Sierra Leonean women dies as a result of complications from pregnancy or childbirth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fistula repair surgery saves lives and makes it possible for women to live normally within the community.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Access to fistula  repair surgery provides patients with:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Restored health and dignity;</li>\r\n	<li>Longer life span;</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to better care for their children;</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to participate in the economy and society; and</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to experience love and romance again.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>", "Fistula Repair Surgery", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "248-revision-v1", "", "", "2015-11-10 08:26:42", "2015-11-10 08:26:42", "", "248", "http://ideafoundation.tk/248-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `gxd_posts` VALUES("331", "5", "2015-11-10 08:28:33", "2015-11-10 08:28:33", "<p>One of the difficulties facing communities under quarantine for Ebola is <a href=\"http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/ebola-virus-outbreak/thousands-break-ebola-quarantine-find-food-sierra-leone-n241016\" target=\"_blank\">a lack of food</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Villagers are prohibited from leaving the village to work in the fields or purchase food. At the same time vendors who bring food to the area are forbidden to enter the area. Because of this getting nutrition for those that are quarantined is rather difficult and disastrous.</p>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"182\"]<img id=\"image_7116894107\" src=\"http://www.theideafoundation.org/s/cc_images/cache_4091519638.jpg?t=1415315529\" alt=\"Residents of the quarantined village of Prejahun with food aid.\" width=\"182\" height=\"158\" /> Residents of the quarantined village of Prejahun with food aid.[/caption]\r\n\r\n<p>Through our in-country partners, IDEA is providing food to individuals, families and villages which are under quarantine, but too remote to attract the services of larger NGOs. As we want to help everyone who is affected by the virus whether they have contracted it or not. Supplies include: fish, rice, onions, oil, tomato paste, and Maggi (a popular seasoning mix.)</p>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>This food:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Provides nutiontional support to promote health;</li>\r\n	<li>Prevents individuals from leaving a quarantined area in search of food for themselves or their children; and</li>\r\n	<li>Reduces stress in a difficult and frightening situation.</li>\r\n</ul></p>", "Food For Quarantined Villages", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "231-revision-v1", "", "", "2015-11-10 08:28:33", "2015-11-10 08:28:33", "", "231", "http://ideafoundation.tk/231-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `gxd_posts` VALUES("333", "5", "2015-11-10 18:05:19", "2015-11-10 18:05:19", "<p>There is a substantial shortage of books in Sierra Leone. Students who are lucky enough to have books often share with several classmates. In addition, many libraries are still short of books following destruction during the war. IDEA supplies appropriate books to elementary and secondary schools as well to universities and public libraries.<p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By supporting educational and public institutions with books, IDEA:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Increases opportunities for education</li>\r\n<li>Helps to expand the knowledge-based infrastructure</li>\r\n<li>Provides the tools for teachers to teach more efficiently and effectively.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis program coordinates with:\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:none\">\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.booksforafrica.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Books for Africa</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://ntnl.org/partners/elc-sierra-leone\" target=\"_blank\">ELCSL</a></li>\r\n<li> <a href=\"http://www.fapl.info/\" target=\"_blank\">Friends of the Aurora Public Library</a></li>\r\n<li> <a href=\"http://www.forgottendiamonds.com/Projects.html\" target=\"_blank\">Forgotten Diamonds</a></li>\r\n<li> <a href=\"http://www.majorsbooks.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Majors Books</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n&nbsp;", "K-12 Textbooks & Library Books", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "266-autosave-v1", "", "", "2015-11-10 18:05:19", "2015-11-10 18:05:19", "", "266", "http://ideafoundation.tk/266-autosave-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
